        <p><strong>Dennis MacAlistair Ritchie</strong> (9 September 1941 - 12 October 2011) was an American computer scientist who "<em>helped shape the digital era.</em>" He created the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('C', 'L'); ?> programming language and, with long-time colleague <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Ken Thompson', 'P'); ?>, the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Unix', 'OS'); ?> operating system. Ritchie and Thompson received the Turing Award from the ACM in 1983, the Hamming Medal from the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('IEEE', 'C'); ?> in 1990 and the National Medal of Technology from President Clinton in 1999.</p>
